@p-l-  According to the [Python documentation](https://docs.python.org/3/reference/compound_stmts.html#the-with-statement), grouping parentheses are only allowed since Python 3.10:

> Changed in version 3.10: Support for using grouping parentheses to break the statement in multiple lines.

That's why the [ubuntu-latest 3.7](https://github.com/secdev/scapy/actions/runs/4046498140/jobs/6959360998) and [ubuntu-latest 3.8](https://github.com/secdev/scapy/actions/runs/4046498140/jobs/6959361199) jobs fail. I'll fix that. (Interestingly, the [ubuntu-latest 3.9](https://github.com/secdev/scapy/actions/runs/4046498140/jobs/6959361370) job doesn't fail, although it should according to the documentation.)

